    <p>Twelve attributes, one honest verdict column — and notice how often that column reads "the bird, not the sex." Every cell is written the way we'd say it to a buyer standing in our kitchen, certificate on the counter. The only rows where sex genuinely decides anything are the reproductive ones. On a phone, tap the sex you're weighing and the table follows you.</p>
