  <!-- S15 FIRST 30 DAYS -->
  <section id="first30">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">How Will a New Grey — Cock or Hen — Settle in the First Month?</h2>
    <img class="sec-img" src="/male-vs-female-african-grey-inside-their-cage.webp" srcset="/male-vs-female-african-grey-inside-their-cage-760.webp 760w, /male-vs-female-african-grey-inside-their-cage.webp 640w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 640px" width="640" height="480" alt="A young male and female African Grey settling in together inside their cage during the first weeks at home, both DNA-sexed captive-bred birds from C.A.Gs in Midland, TX" loading="lazy">
    <p>The sex you choose changes almost nothing about the first month — the arc below is the same for a cock or a hen, and our <a href="/african-grey-parrot-care-guide/">African Grey care guide</a> picks up where day 30 ends. Teri walks every buyer through the same four phases:</p>
    <h3 class="cag-h3">Which Four Phases Does Every New Grey Move Through?</h3>
    <p>Screenshot this before pickup day — it separates "my new grey hates me" panic from recognizing a bird exactly on schedule.</p>
    <img class="sec-img" src="/male-vs-female-african-grey-parrots-for-sale-relationship-journey.webp" srcset="/male-vs-female-african-grey-parrots-for-sale-relationship-journey-760.webp 760w, /male-vs-female-african-grey-parrots-for-sale-relationship-journey.webp 640w" sizes="(max-width:900px) 92vw, 640px" width="640" height="480" alt="The relationship journey of a new African Grey and its owner over the first month — a hand-tame captive-bred Grey stepping up and bonding, sex making no difference to the adjustment arc" loading="lazy">
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="tl-c"><span class="tl-n">1</span><b>Days 1–3 · Settling</b><p>Expect a quiet bird perching low and eating mostly when unwatched. Day-two chattiness is individual, never a cock-or-hen thing — early test-mumbling and a reserved first week are equally on schedule.</p></div>
      <div class="tl-c"><span class="tl-n">2</span><b>Week 1 · Mapping</b><p>Your grey is memorizing the house — footsteps, feeding times, which sounds mean what. Be deliberately boring; predictability is the whole assignment.</p></div>
      <div class="tl-c"><span class="tl-n">3</span><b>Week 2 · Trust</b><p>Voluntary step-ups arrive, treats are taken softly, and the first borrowed noises of <em>your</em> household start playing back.</p></div>
      <div class="tl-c"><span class="tl-n">4</span><b>Weeks 3–4 · Stabilizing</b><p>The real personality surfaces — and this is the week our check-in call lands. Whichever sex you chose, you hold our direct line for the entire first month.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

