  <!-- S22 KEEP LEARNING (18A blog cards) -->
  <section id="learn">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">Sex Settled — What Should You Research Next?</h2>
    <p>Choosing between cock and hen was the easy part — the grey itself is a four-decade commitment. These three guides cover what careful buyers study next: the species facts worth knowing cold, the cage that should be assembled before your bird lands, and how a Grey measures against an Eclectus if you're still weighing parrots.</p>
